"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-03-paris-2024-olympics-chukwuma-falters-enekwechi-misses-out-on-shot-put-medal\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Team Nigeria's Rosemary Chukwuma failed to make it to the final of the women's 100m at the 2024 Olympic Games.  Chukwuma faltered in the semi-finals of the event, finishing in last place.  She started the race in a commanding fashion but failed to sustain the momentum.  In the men's shot put final, Chukwuebuka Enekwechi finished fifth with a throw of 21.42m missing out on a medal.  USA's Ryan Crouser won gold medal with a throw of 22.90m.  His compatriot Joe Kovacs won silver with a throw of 22.15m, while Jamaica's Rajindra Campbell came in third with a throw of 22.15m.  Transfer: Midfielder rejects move to join Mourinho at Fenerbahce  Transfer: Conte only wants Lukaku at Napoli, snubs Osimhen again  Anambra: I will not exchange words with Soludo - YPP governorship candidate Chukwuma  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"